# Patch 0008 — Workspace notes (Kavacha platform plan, MVP item).
#
# What: local notes attached to each space. "Workspace Notes" opens a panel
# (space actions menu or the command palette) with an autosaving textarea —
# 500ms debounce plus a flush on close. Notes are stored per-profile in
# kavacha-notes.json (JSONFile, keyed by workspace uuid), deliberately NOT
# on the space object: they would bloat the session file and ride
# Mozilla-account sync. They stay on-device until Kavacha's own E2E sync
# (Phase 5) can carry them. Empty notes are deleted from the store.
# Last-write-wins across windows (single shared store per profile).
# Why a patch: the panel lives in Zen's popupset and the open/save logic in
# the spaces manager; the notes store itself is new Kavacha state.
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl,
#          src/zen/urlbar/ZenUBGlobalActions.sys.mjs,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl.
# Applies on top of 0007.
